.TH VOLS 1 "March 2026" "bas-cpp" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vols \- list local volumes detected by bas-cpp
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vols
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vols
enumerates local volumes known to the bas-cpp volume subsystem and prints
one line per volume.
.PP
Each line contains the following tab-separated fields:
.IP \(bu 2
Mount point or root path
.IP \(bu 2
Device path (or \- if unknown)
.IP \(bu 2
Volume type
.IP \(bu 2
Label
.IP \(bu 2
UUID
.PP
The output is intended primarily for human inspection and simple scripting.
.SH OPTIONS
This command currently takes no options.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The
.B vols
command exits with status 0 on success and a non-zero status on error.
.SH AUTHORS
Written as part of the bas-cpp project.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bas-cpp (7)

